article.headline: Fordham 38, Georgetown 31
article.story: NEW YORK -- Ryan Higgins passed for 305 yards and two touchdowns and Carlton Koonce ran for two scores as Fordham beat Georgetown 38-31 Saturday in Patriot League play. The Rams (4-2, 1-0) got three field goals from Patrick Murray and a 2-point conversion pass from Higgins to Dan Light. Higgins completed 29 of 38 passes. Greg Wilson caught a 19-yard touchdown in the first quarter and Blake Wayne a 25-yarder in the third. Then Higgins' conversion pass to Light gave Fordham a 31-24 lead, after Koonce's 44-yard scoring run earlier in the quarter. Kevin Macari scored twice for Georgetown (3-3, 0-1) on a 4-yard run in the first quarter and a 2-yard pass from Stephen Skon in the third. Skon's 5-yard scoring pass to Nick Campanella put the Hoyas up 24-23. Campanella's 7-yard run in the fourth tied it 31-all, but Koonce's 1-yard run with 9 minutes remaining won it.
